: [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Mitigation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Always"}, {"type": "text", "text": " perform code review after AI-assisted resolution\n- Run tests post-resolution\n- Use CI/CD pipelines to catch integration issues\n- Require 2+ reviewer approvals for critical files"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key Takeaways"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n1. Merge conflicts happen when branches change the same line differently—Git needs human help\n2. Pull requests + code review prevent bad merges and catch conflicts early\n3. Keep PRs small, pull from "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "main"}, {"type": "text", "text": " frequently, and use helper branches for complex conflicts\n4. AI tools (JetBrains AI, CodeGPT) speed up resolution but "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "human review is still mandatory"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n5. Proper resolution maintains code quality, team collaboration, and clean commit history"}]}]}}